Add mali-fbdev video driver for PowerVR GE8300 (TrimUI Brick vendor kernel).

The mali-fbdev driver opens /dev/fb0 and creates an EGL surface via
EGL_DEFAULT_DISPLAY (EGL_API_FB), which is how PowerVR GE8300's libEGL.so
exposes GPU rendering on the vendor framebuffer kernel.

Driver source is adapted from Knulli's SDL2 PVR patch with the SDL2_POWERVR_GE8300
window-type specialisation (EGLNativeWindowType instead of fbdev_window struct).

Requires: SDL2_AUTORECONF = YES (set in sdl2.mk by PanicOS Makefile).

